properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued January 27 at 9:41AM AKST until January 27 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
CORRECTION FOR A TYPO IN ZONE 125

...BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 PM AKST THIS
EVENING FOR THOMPSON PASS...

* WHAT...Blizzard conditions expected. Total snow accumulations
of 6 to 10 inches. Winds gusting as high as 50 mph. Whiteout
conditions expected at times.

* WHERE...Thompson Pass.

* WHEN...Until 9 PM AKST this evening.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. Widespread blowing
snow could significantly reduce visibility. The dangerously
cold wind chills as low as 40 below zero could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 10 minutes.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.
